    "title": "Crashing on Linux (Raspberry Pi)",
    "body": "**What behavior did you expect?**\r\nBitcoin keeps running on my Raspberry Pi 4 (2GB RAM)\r\n\r\n**What was the actual behavior (provide screenshots if the issue is GUI-related)?**\r\nEvery day it has to be rerun multiple times due to crashing with the error:\r\n\"terminate called without an active exception\"\r\n\r\n**How reliably can you reproduce the issue, what are the steps to do so?**\r\nJust turn it on and wait for hours I guess.\r\n\r\n**What version of Bitcoin Core are you using, where did you get it (website, self-compiled, etc)?**\r\nBitcoin Core version v0.18.0\r\nGot it from https://bitcoin.org/en/bitcoin-core/\r\n\r\n**What type of machine are you observing the error on (OS/CPU and disk type)?**\r\nRaspberry Pi 4 with external 1TB HDD.\r\n \r\n**For the GUI-related issue on Linux provide names and versions of a distro, a desktop environment and a graphical shell (if relevant).**\r\nLatest Raspbian distributive.\r\n",
